Across all linkage mechanisms, the bias of β^^𝛽\hat{\beta} is generally negative, as false links attenuate the estimates towards zero. When the mechanism is LCAR, SNL, or NL, the Bayesian, weighting, and likelihood-based methods have generally small biases. Across the LCAR, SNL, and NL mechanisms, HZ exhibits small biases, but also has the largest SEs among all methods, which results in coverage rates well above 95%.

to construct comparison vectors. and mixing proportions with reasonable accuracy.
